### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 7](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 7:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 7:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#001.md), They of Kirjath-jearim bring
the ark into the house of Abinadab, and sanctify Eleazar, his son to
keep it; [Sa1 7:2](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#002.md), After twenty years,
[Sa1 7:3](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#003.md), the Israelites, by Samuel's
means, solemnly repent at Mizpeh; [Sa1
7:7](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#007.md), While Samuel prays and
sacrifices, the Lord discomfits the Philistines by thunder at Eben-ezer;
[Sa1 7:13](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#013.md), The Philistines are
subdued; [Sa1 7:15](../../../bib/kjv/sa1007.htm#015.md), Samuel judges
Israel.

