northern parts of the country could attend him; when at Gilgal, the
tribe of Benjamin and those beyond Jordan could have easy access to him;
and when at Mizpeh, he was within the reach of Judah, Simeon, and Gad,
but at Ramah was the place of his ordinary abode; and there he held his
court, for there he judged Israel, and as it is probable that Shiloh was
